Intensity arc:     {{ intensity_arc }} (peaks before interruption, drops sharply after)

{{ speakers_block(speakers) }}
SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
The presence of a witness transforms the dynamic:
  1. Pre-interruption peak — the couple is in a heated argument or the perpetrator is escalating.
  2. Interruption — third party knocks, calls out, or enters unexpectedly.
  3. Face-saving — both parties immediately change tone in front of the witness.
  4. Managed interaction — polite or awkward exchange with the third party.
  5. Post-interruption — third party leaves; scene ends before violence can resume.
This is a negative example because no violence occurs — the witness prevents it.

